title: Compiler crash with huge struct

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

body:
When compiling the below struct, I get a compiler error:

```
Could not compile `ceph`.

Caused by:
  Process didn't exit successfully: `rustc src/lib.rs --crate-name ceph --crate-type lib -g --out-dir /Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug --emit=dep-info,link -L dependency=/Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug -L dependency=/Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug/deps --extern rustc_serialize=/Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug/deps/librustc_serialize-7ff5bfc027146194.rlib --extern unix_socket=/Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug/deps/libunix_socket-e210e3259e35e66c.rlib --extern log=/Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug/deps/liblog-35171053ffe7ab96.rlib --extern regex=/Users/icey/Projects/all/ceph-rs/target/debug/deps/libregex-c5abedf84fe61ddb.rlib` (signal: 11)
```
